To make a function a friend of the template class `PFArray` in Display 16.5, you need to declare the function prototype inside the class definition and use the `friend` keyword. Here's how you can make a function `myFriendFunction` a friend of the `PFArray` class:

```cpp
template<class T>
class PFArray {
public:
  // ...

private:
  // ...

  // Declare the friend function prototype inside the class
  friend void myFriendFunction(const PFArray<T>& pfa);
};
```

In this example, the function `myFriendFunction` is declared as a friend function inside the `PFArray` class template. This allows the `myFriendFunction` to access the private and protected members of the `PFArray` class.

